  "text": "that is, a free resolution of the O-module O m 0 /J in U . By Hilbert's zyzygy theorem we can assume that N \u2264 n. We have an induced complex of (trivial) vector bundles (2.6), where rank E k = m k , which is pointwise exact outside the zero set Z of f 1 (if m 0 \u2265 2, Z is the set where f 1 does not have optimal rank.) Let us equip these vector bundles with any Hermitian metrics, for instance trivial metrics with respect to global frames, and let R and U be the associated currents. A main result in [CITATION_1] is that the exactness of (2.10)",
